# Implementation Plan - Immersive Video Mode

The goal is to hide the floating navigation bar when the user scrolls to the video section, creating a distraction-free viewing experience.

## Proposed Changes

### CSS
#### [MODIFY] [f1.css](file:///c:/Users/hp/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/sona-landing-page/css/f1.css)
- Update `.pill-nav`:
    - Add `transition: all 0.5s cubic-bezier(0.2, 0.8, 0.2, 1);` (matching other smooth animations).
- Add `.pill-nav.nav-hidden`:
    - `transform: translateX(-50%) translateY(-200%);` (Move up and out, maintaining horizontal center).
    - `opacity: 0;`

### JavaScript
#### [MODIFY] [index.html](file:///c:/Users/hp/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/sona-landing-page/index.html)
- Update the existing `IntersectionObserver` for `.video-reveal-section`.
- Get reference to `document.querySelector('.pill-nav')`.
- Inside the callback:
